<!-- field-start:notes -->

<a name="miscellaneous-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Editorial Notes</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="priorprovisions-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:priorprovisions-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Prior Provisions</h4>

<p class="note-body">Prior section 3108 was renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('5308', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 5308 of this title</span>.</p>

<p class="note-body">Provisions similar to those comprising this section were contained in former <span onclick="openDocument('1504', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 1504 of this title</span> prior to the general revision of this chapter by <pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466</pLaw>.</p>
<!-- field-end:priorprovisions-note -->

<a name="amendment-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:amendment-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Amendments</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2015</b>-Subsec. (b)(4). <pLaw congress="114" isPrivate="false" number="58">Pub. L. 114&ndash;58</pLaw> inserted "the" before "rehabilitation program concerned".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2012</b>-Subsec. (a)(2). <pLaw congress="112" isPrivate="false" number="154">Pub. L. 112&ndash;154</pLaw> designated existing provisions as subpar. (A) and added subpar. (B).</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2011</b>-Subsec. (b)(4). <pLaw congress="111" isPrivate="false" number="377">Pub. L. 111&ndash;377</pLaw> added par. (4).</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>2006</b>-Subsec. (g)(1). <pLaw congress="109" isPrivate="false" number="461">Pub. L. 109&ndash;461</pLaw> substituted "local, or other penal institution or correctional facility" for "or local penal institution".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1996</b>-Subsec. (a)(2). <pLaw congress="104" isPrivate="false" number="275">Pub. L. 104&ndash;275,</pLaw> &sect;101(g)(1), substituted "while satisfactorily following a program of employment services provided under <span onclick="openDocument('3104', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 3104(a)(5) of this title</span>" for "following the conclusion of such pursuit".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (f)(1)(A). <pLaw congress="104" isPrivate="false" number="275">Pub. L. 104&ndash;275,</pLaw> &sect;101(g)(2)(A), inserted "eligible for and" after "veteran is" and substituted "<span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span>" for "<span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span> or 34" and "enrolled under <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span>" for "enrolled under either <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span> or <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '34'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 34</span>".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (f)(1)(B). <pLaw congress="104" isPrivate="false" number="275">Pub. L. 104&ndash;275,</pLaw> &sect;101(g)(2)(B), substituted "<span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span>" for "<span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span> or 34".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1994</b>-Subsec. (c)(2). <pLaw congress="103" isPrivate="false" number="446">Pub. L. 103&ndash;446</pLaw> inserted "or federally recognized Indian tribe" after "local government agency".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1992</b>-Subsec. (b). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="568">Pub. L. 102&ndash;568,</pLaw> &sect;405(b), designated existing provisions as par. (1) and added pars. (2) and (3).</p>

<p class="note-body">
<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="568">Pub. L. 102&ndash;568,</pLaw> &sect;405(a), increased the monthly rehabilitation subsistence allowance for eligible veterans in column II from $333, $250, $167, $291, $333, $333, $250, and $167 to $366, $275, $184, $320, $366, $366, $275, and $184; in column III from $413, $310, $207, $352, $413, $413, $310, and $207 to $454, $341, $228, $387, $454, $454, $341, and $228; in column IV from $486, $364, $244, $405, $486, $486, $364, and $244 to $535, $400, $268, $446, $535, $535, $$400, and $268; and in column V from $35, $27, $18, $26, $35, $35, $27, and $18 to $39, $30, $20, $29, $39, $39, $30, and $20, respectively.</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1991</b>-<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(a), renumbered <span onclick="openDocument('1508', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 1508 of this title</span> as this section.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (a)(3). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "3106(a)" for "1506(a)" and "3105(b)" for "1505(b)".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (c)(2). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "3115(a)(1)" for "1515(a)(1)".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="16">Pub. L. 102&ndash;16</pLaw> inserted ",&nbsp;State, or local government" after "Federal".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (f)(2). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "3104(a)(3)" for "1504(a)(3)".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (h). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "1114(j)" for "314(j)" in two places.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (i). <pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="83">Pub. L. 102&ndash;83,</pLaw> &sect;5(c)(1), substituted "3680(d)" for "1780(d)".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1989</b>-Subsec. (a)(1), (2). <pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> &sect;423(b)(1)(A), substituted "Secretary" for "Administrator".</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (b). <pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> &sect;423(b)(1)(A), substituted "Secretary" for "Administrator".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> &sect;402(a), increased the monthly rehabilitation subsistence allowance for eligible veterans in column II from $310, $233, $155, $271, $310, $310, $233, and $155 to $333, $250, $167, $291, $333, $333, $250, and $167; in column III from $384, $288, $193, $327, $384, $384, $288, and $193 to $413, $310, $207, $352, $413, $413, $310, and $207; in column IV from $452, $339, $227, $377, $452, $452, $339, and $227 to $486, $364, $244, $405, $486, $486, $364, and $244; in column V from $33, $25, $17, $24, $33, $33, $25, and $17 to $35, $27, $18, $26, $35, $35, $27, and $18, respectively.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsecs. (c)(1) to (f)(1)(A). <pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> &sect;423(b)(1)(A), substituted "Secretary" for "Administrator" wherever appearing.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (h). <pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> &sect;423(b)(1)(B), substituted "Department of Veterans Affairs" for "Veterans' Administration".</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1984</b>-Subsec. (b). <pLaw congress="98" isPrivate="false" number="543">Pub. L. 98&ndash;543</pLaw> increased the monthly rehabilitation subsistence allowance for eligible veterans in column II from $282, $212, $141, $246, $282, $282, $212, and $141 to $310, $233, $155, $271, $310, $310, $233, and $155; in column III from $349, $262, $175, $297, $349, $349, $262, and $175 to $384, $288, $193, $323, $384, $384, $288, and $193; in column IV from $411, $308, $206, $343, $411, $411, $308, and $206 to $452, $339, $227, $377, $452, $452, $339, and $227; in column V from $30, $23, $15, $22, $30, $30, $23, and $15 to $33, $25, $17, $24, $33, $33, $25, and $17, respectively.</p>

<p class="note-body">Subsec. (f)(1)(A), (B). <pLaw congress="98" isPrivate="false" number="525">Pub. L. 98&ndash;525</pLaw> inserted references to <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', '30'); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">chapter 30</span> of this title.</p>

<p class="note-body">
<b>1982</b>-Subsec. (g)(2). <pLaw congress="97" isPrivate="false" number="306">Pub. L. 97&ndash;306</pLaw> inserted "not" after "shall" and struck out "if the Administrator determines that all the veteran's living expenses are being defrayed by a Federal, State, or local government" at end.</p>

<br class="Q04">
<!-- field-end:amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">
<strong>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</strong>
</h4>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->

<a name="effectivedate-amendment-note"></a>
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-amendment-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 2012 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">Amendment by <pLaw congress="112" isPrivate="false" number="154">Pub. L. 112&ndash;154</pLaw> effective on the date that is one year after Aug. 6, 2012, see section 701(g) of <pLaw congress="112" isPrivate="false" number="154">Pub. L. 112&ndash;154,</pLaw> set out as an Effective Date note under <span onclick="openDocument('2109', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 2109 of this title</span>.</p>

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 2011 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=124&page=4126" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="111" isPrivate="false" number="377">Pub. L. 111&ndash;377,</pLaw> title II, &sect;205(b), Jan. 4, 2011, <statuteAtLarge page="4126" volume="124">124 Stat. 4126</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, provided that: "The amendment made by this section [amending this section] shall take effect on August 1, 2011."</p>

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1992 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=106&page=4339" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="102" isPrivate="false" number="568">Pub. L. 102&ndash;568,</pLaw> title IV, &sect;405(c), Oct. 29, 1992, <statuteAtLarge page="4339" volume="106">106 Stat. 4339</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, provided that: "The amendments made by subsections (a) and (b) [amending this section] shall take effect on October 1, 1993."</p>

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1989 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=103&page=2078" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="101" isPrivate="false" number="237">Pub. L. 101&ndash;237,</pLaw> title IV, &sect;402(b), Dec. 18, 1989, <statuteAtLarge page="2078" volume="103">103 Stat. 2078</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, provided that: "The amendment made by this section [amending this section] shall take effect on January 1, 1990."</p>

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1984 Amendment</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=98&page=2743" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="98" isPrivate="false" number="543">Pub. L. 98&ndash;543,</pLaw> title II, &sect;205, Oct. 24, 1984, <statuteAtLarge page="2743" volume="98">98 Stat. 2743</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, provided that: "The amendments made by this part [part A (&sect;&sect;201&ndash;205) of title II of <pLaw congress="98" isPrivate="false" number="543">Pub. L. 98&ndash;543,</pLaw> see Tables for classification] shall take effect as of October 1, 1984."</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-amendment-note -->
<!-- field-start:effectivedate-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date; Veterans Pursuing Program of Vocational Rehabilitation Under This Chapter</h4>

<p class="note-body">Section effective Oct. 1, 1980, and during period beginning on Oct. 1, 1980, and ending on Mar. 31, 1981, the provisions of this section, as added by <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=94&page=2178" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> title I, &sect;101(a), Oct. 17, 1980, <statuteAtLarge page="2178" volume="94">94 Stat. 2178</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, shall apply to veterans pursuing a program of vocational rehabilitation training under this chapter in the same manner as former <span onclick="openDocument('1504', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 1504 of this title</span> applied to veterans pursuing such a program under this chapter on Sept. 30, 1980, see section 802(a)(2), (4) of <pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> set out as an Effective Date note under <span onclick="openDocument('3100', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">section 3100 of this title</span>.</p>
<!-- field-end:effectivedate-note -->
<!-- field-start:miscellaneous-note -->

<h4 class="note-head">Extension of Payment of Vocational Rehabilitation Subsistence Allowances</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=134&page=634" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="116" isPrivate="false" number="140">Pub. L. 116&ndash;140,</pLaw> &sect;8, Apr. 28, 2020, <statuteAtLarge page="634" volume="134">134 Stat. 634</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, which temporarily allowed for additional subsistence allowances for certain veterans, was repealed by <a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=136&page=6128" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="117" isPrivate="false" number="333">Pub. L. 117&ndash;333,</pLaw> &sect;4(b), Jan. 5, 2023, <statuteAtLarge page="6128" volume="136">136 Stat. 6128</statuteAtLarge>
</a>.</p>

<h4 class="note-head">Applicability of Subsection (g)(1) to Apportionments Made Before October 17, 1980</h4>

<p class="note-body">
<a href="/statviewer.htm?volume=94&page=2186" target="_blank" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" style="text-decoration: none;color: #0F0D61;">
<pLaw congress="96" isPrivate="false" number="466">Pub. L. 96&ndash;466,</pLaw> title I, &sect;101(c), Oct. 17, 1980, <statuteAtLarge page="2186" volume="94">94 Stat. 2186</statuteAtLarge>
</a>, provided that: "The provisions of section 1508(g)(1) [now 3108(g)(1)] of <span onclick="openDocument('', '38', ''); return false;" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none';" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline';" class="stdref">title 38, United States Code</span>, as added by subsection (a) shall not apply to an apportionment made under section 3107(c) [now 5307(c)] of such title before the date of the enactment of this Act [Oct. 17, 1980]."</p>
<!-- field-end:miscellaneous-note -->
<!-- field-end:notes -->





